cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.CY

This paper discusses the correct configuration of web servers to ensure secure communication, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). It also involves the analysis of data over a period of time, which could be related to software engineering (cs.SE). The use of a service to test the correctness of a web server configuration involves network security (cs.NI) and system security (cs.SI). Finally, the analysis of the relationship between the number of test-runs and the resulting quality of a TLS configuration could be related to cybersecurity (cs.CY).
